  "summary": "TPC-H workload dominated by lineitem (60M rows) with heavy analytical scanning. Q1 and Q6 are single-table scans with selective filtering and aggregation—both highly parallelizable with morsel-driven approach on 64 cores. Q3 is more complex: 3-way star join (customer→orders→lineitem) with pre-filters reducing intermediate sizes significantly; critical path is lineitem scan (30.8M rows after ship-date filter) joined with filtered orders (7.3M rows). Bottleneck: Q3's lineitem scan and hash join phases; Q1/Q6 are I/O-bound on lineitem. Key levers: (1) parallel morsel-driven scans with thread-local aggregation, (2) partitioned hash joins to leverage CPU caches, (3) predicate pushdown (filter orders before join), (4) SIMD-accelerated filtering for discount/quantity predicates."
